OL,7,FBut she says the trader is not the
OL,8,Fonly one to have let her down - she
OL,9,Fhad expected far more help from
OL,10,FTrading Standards who did not
OL,11,Fprosecute.
OL,13,F"It's been a really stressful
OL,14,Fexperience for the whole family," Ms
OL,15,FDickenson said.
OL,17,F"We didn't think when we started this
OL,18,Fproject that we would have no recourse
OL,19,Fif things were to go wrong.
